<p> Meanwhile, South Africa is set to start rolling out the Sinovac-CoronaVac vaccine manufactured in China after it received conditional approval from the South African Health Products Regulatory Authority (SAHPRA). The Chinese-made vaccine is being used in many countries and it has been shown to be effective in preventing severe COVID-19 disease and death. But there are some questions about its general efficacy. CEO of the SAHPRA, Dr. Boitumelo Semete-Makokotlela discuss the Sinovac-CoronaVac vaccine:  